                <mxCell id="EdAH23wTT8TAoaTBZzOQ-26" value="&lt;b&gt;Day 1 vs Scale&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Day 1:&lt;/b&gt; Orchestrator submits jobs via HTTP to the K8s Job Controller. Pod reports status, heartbeats, and results back through the Workflow API (never touches the State Store directly). LangGraph Checkpointer handles resume across the approval gate.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Scale:&lt;/b&gt; Orchestrator can publish to the bus and a Job Dispatcher pod in AKS (or KEDA ScaledJob) consumes execute-jobs messages and creates K8s Jobs. To be used when decoupling across clusters/clouds or per-message autoscaling is required.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Another approach&lt;/b&gt;:&lt;br&gt;Control plane triggers code execution via github actions; github actions responsible for the execution layer workflow&lt;div&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#fff8dc;strokeColor=#999999;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacingLeft=8;spacingTop=8;spacingRight=8;fontSize=11;" vertex="1" parent="1">
